Step 7: Reflection and Analysis
Markdown Cell:

Is the model reliable? Yes, the R-squared score and low MAE justify that the model can reliably predict delivery times.

Limitations: The model only uses two features. It ignores traffic, weather, and courier experience, which are also important.

Strongest Contributor: Distance_km contributes the most, as it has a higher correlation and a larger impact on total travel time.

Predictor Removal: If Distance_km were removed, the model would lose its most important signal, causing the error (RMSE) to increase significantly.

Correlation vs Causation: Correlation implies causation here; a longer distance physically requires more travel time, directly causing the delivery time to increase.

